  "body": "What?\r\nThe following pod yaml works on 1.4 cluster:\r\n```yaml\r\napiVersion: v1\r\nkind: Pod\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: nginx\r\n  labels:\r\n    name: nginx\r\n  annotations:\r\n    pod.beta.kubernetes.io/init-containers: '[\r\n      {\r\n        \"Name\": \"fun\",\r\n        \"Image\": \"alpine\",\r\n        \"Command\": [\r\n          \"/bin/sh\",\r\n          \"-c\",\r\n          \"sleep 5\"\r\n        ],\r\n        \"Env\": [\r\n          {\r\n            \"Name\": \"MY_POD_IP\",\r\n            \"ValueFrom\": {\r\n              \"FieldRef\": {\r\n                \"APIVersion\": \"\",\r\n                \"FieldPath\": \"status.podIP\"\r\n              }\r\n            }\r\n          }\r\n        ]\r\n      }\r\n    ]'\r\nspec:\r\n  containers:\r\n  - name: nginx\r\n    image: nginx\r\n    ports:\r\n    - containerPort: 80\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, creating it against 1.5.1 or master branch 84d0fbd gives the following error:\r\n```\r\nThe Pod \"nginx\" is invalid: spec.initContainers[0].env[0].valueFrom.fieldRef.apiVersion: Required value\r\n```\r\n",
